enum RtpPayloadType

Enumeration for supported rtp payload (RFC3551) In fact, this enmu is used as packet format. But for static payload type codec, packet format is equal to payload type. For example, AMR-WB packet format are 77 ~ 85, but the RTP payload type of AMR-WB should be dynamic payload (>96). Packet format and payload type can be assigned in TAPI rtk_SetRtpPayloadType() separately.
